# Qovery Provider

The [Qovery](https://www.qovery.com/) provider is used to interact with the resources supported by Qovery.
The provider needs to be configured with the proper credentials before it can be used.

## Authentication

The Qovery provider offers the following methods for providing credentials:

- **Static credentials** — Set the `token` argument in the provider configuration.
- **Environment variable** — Set the `QOVERY_API_TOKEN` environment variable.

### Obtaining an API Token

To generate an API token, navigate to your [Qovery Console](https://console.qovery.com) > Settings > API Tokens.
For more details, see the [Qovery API Token documentation](https://hub.qovery.com/docs/using-qovery/interface/cli/#generate-api-token).

### Using Environment Variables

```shell
export QOVERY_API_TOKEN="your-api-token"
```

